Fig. 3
a–c shows TEM images of the GO, r-GO, and GQDs samples, respectively. Their sheet-like morphology and surface area are observable. Also, the high transparency of these nanosheets confirms their scalable atomic thickness. To study the edge formation of the samples, SEM images were taken from the cross-section of GO and GQD film samples (Fig. 4
). The edge-shape of the GO and GQDs are observable, during the film formation due to the presence of functional groups on the basal plane and edges, the GO layers laid on each other with more distance than GQD layers.
